            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Mathematically, a Cartesian product is a set, so a Cartesian product does &lt;i&gt;not&lt;/i&gt; contain duplicates. On the other hand, &lt;code&gt;itertools.product&lt;/code&gt; will have duplicates in the output if the inputs have duplicates. So &lt;code&gt;itertools.product&lt;/code&gt; is not strictly speaking the Cartesian product, unless you wrap the inputs in &lt;code&gt;set&lt;/code&gt;, as mentioned by @CamilB.&lt;/span&gt;

